<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
      Hardened Runtime entitlements for the notarized Developer ID build.

      • automation.apple-events — REQUIRED. Under the Hardened Runtime, sending
        Apple Events (we drive System Events to flip Dark/Light) is blocked
        unless the app carries this entitlement. The user is still prompted for
        Automation permission on first use (TCC); this entitlement only permits
        the app to ask.

      Deliberately NOT included:
      • App Sandbox — a Developer ID app is not sandboxed; sandboxing is
        incompatible with driving System Events and reading the global appearance.
      • disable-library-validation — NOT needed. We dlopen the private
        CoreBrightness framework for Night Shift, but it is Apple-signed, so the
        Hardened Runtime's library validation already permits loading it. We keep
        validation ON for security.
      • get-task-allow — must be absent for a Developer ID / notarized build.
      CoreLocation and local notifications need no entitlement for a non-sandboxed
      Developer ID app; their Info.plist usage strings suffice.
    -->
    <key>com.apple.security.automation.apple-events</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
